
[1]intellectual

   INTELLECT'UAL, a.

   1. Relating to the intellect or understanding; belonging to the mind;
   performed by the understanding; mental; as intellectual power or
   operations.

   2. Ideal; perceived by the intellect; existing in the understanding; as
   an intellectual scene.

   3. Having the power of understanding; as an intellectual being.

   4. Relating to the understanding; treating of the mind; as intellectual
   philosophy, now sometimes called mental philosophy.

      INTELLECT'UAL, n. The intellect or understanding. [Little used.]
